WEBVTT

00:00:41.396 --> 00:00:44.066
NO TAIL TO TELL

00:00:48.987 --> 00:00:50.364
And as for you.

00:00:50.906 --> 00:00:52.491
I'll be coming for you soon.

00:00:54.576 --> 00:00:55.911
No!

00:01:04.753 --> 00:01:05.921
{\an8}Mr. Lee.

00:01:07.172 --> 00:01:08.965
{\an8}Hey. Did you get it?

00:01:09.716 --> 00:01:10.801
{\an8}Yes, sir.

00:01:12.094 --> 00:01:13.970
{\an8}But what do you need this for?

00:01:14.054 --> 00:01:15.097
{\an8}Move, damn it.

00:01:28.527 --> 00:01:32.406
{\an8}I was… thinking about this all wrong.

00:01:33.490 --> 00:01:34.658
{\an8}Pardon?

00:01:34.741 --> 00:01:37.452
{\an8}I'm done shaking like an idiot

00:01:38.286 --> 00:01:40.247
{\an8}over those wretched things.

00:01:41.498 --> 00:01:44.835
{\an8}Sorcery, spirits, whatever.
I'll just shoot them all dead.

00:01:50.257 --> 00:01:51.466
We humans

00:01:53.135 --> 00:01:55.053
have our own ways.

00:02:07.232 --> 00:02:11.319
EPISODE 11
THE WAY OF HUMANS

00:02:12.529 --> 00:02:15.407
{\an8}THIRTY HOURS AGO

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:18.285
{\an8}SUNCHEON STADIUM

00:02:26.543 --> 00:02:27.419
Eun-ho.

00:02:31.131 --> 00:02:32.466
Are you okay?

00:02:44.561 --> 00:02:45.562
What's wrong?

00:02:50.192 --> 00:02:51.568
I don't know.

00:02:52.194 --> 00:02:54.029
I think it was just a dream.

00:02:54.821 --> 00:02:56.323
It has to be.

00:02:58.825 --> 00:03:01.203
I guess I'm just anxious.

00:03:03.288 --> 00:03:04.539
Anxious about what?

00:03:06.166 --> 00:03:07.209
It's just…

00:03:09.127 --> 00:03:10.921
This isn't just a breeze.

00:03:11.755 --> 00:03:13.840
A storm is about to hit.

00:03:16.802 --> 00:03:18.386
What are you thinking about?

00:03:19.429 --> 00:03:20.889
- What?
- Man…

00:03:20.972 --> 00:03:23.225
Anyway, what happened to the coach?

00:03:24.893 --> 00:03:27.604
The game's about to start.
Why isn't he here yet?

00:03:27.687 --> 00:03:29.981
We don't even have a starting lineup.

00:03:32.359 --> 00:03:34.945
Don't you think
Coach has been acting weird lately?

00:03:35.737 --> 00:03:37.614
Do you think he got a scouting offer?

00:03:38.365 --> 00:03:41.201
Is he dumping us mid-season
for another team?

00:03:41.284 --> 00:03:43.578
Don't talk nonsense.

00:03:44.246 --> 00:03:45.789
Guys, it's not like that.

00:03:45.872 --> 00:03:48.208
Why not? It could happen.

00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:52.337
He's right. Sure, Coach has always
ranked last in the fourth division,

00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:57.425
and his playing career wasn't remarkable.
His tactics are old-school,

00:03:58.051 --> 00:04:00.053
his training predictable,

00:04:00.136 --> 00:04:02.556
but that doesn't mean
he couldn't get an offer.

00:04:02.639 --> 00:04:04.307
You know, Si-yeol,

00:04:04.391 --> 00:04:07.811
you have a habit of looking down
on our coach way too much.

00:04:08.979 --> 00:04:10.772
Whoa! Hi, Coach.

00:04:10.856 --> 00:04:12.983
Why don't you just badmouth me,
you punk?

00:04:13.066 --> 00:04:15.652
Coach, why are you so late?

00:04:16.278 --> 00:04:17.737
What about the starting lineup?

00:04:17.821 --> 00:04:19.573
We don't even have any tactics,

00:04:19.656 --> 00:04:22.284
and we haven't analyzed
the opposing team at all.

00:04:22.367 --> 00:04:23.702
How are we supposed to play?

00:04:23.785 --> 00:04:25.203
Forget that. Don't worry too much.

00:04:25.287 --> 00:04:28.248
Anyway, that's not what matters today.

00:04:28.331 --> 00:04:30.375
I have a really important announcement.

00:04:31.251 --> 00:04:32.460
What?

00:04:33.003 --> 00:04:35.213
What are you doing out there?
Come on in.

00:04:40.343 --> 00:04:44.306
From now on, she'll be working
with our team as our new GM.

00:04:44.389 --> 00:04:45.849
This is Ms. Hong Yeon-su.

00:04:45.932 --> 00:04:47.642
Come on. Let's give her a hand.

00:04:51.438 --> 00:04:54.065
Okay… but Coach,

00:04:54.149 --> 00:04:55.483
the game's about to start,

00:04:55.567 --> 00:04:58.361
and this is supposed to be
your big announcement?

00:04:58.445 --> 00:05:02.115
Not exactly. There's something else.

00:05:02.198 --> 00:05:05.744
Well, what's your match fee these days?

00:05:05.827 --> 00:05:08.121
It's… 50,000 won.

00:05:08.204 --> 00:05:10.832
- Right. And your win bonus?
- It's 300,000 won.

00:05:12.375 --> 00:05:14.920
Starting today, our players' match fee

00:05:15.003 --> 00:05:18.006
won't be 50,000 won anymore.
It will be 200,000 won.

00:05:18.673 --> 00:05:19.716
Did she say 200,000 won?

00:05:19.799 --> 00:05:21.760
- It's 200,000 won?
- 200,000?

00:05:22.677 --> 00:05:24.721
And the win bonus went up a bit too.

00:05:25.847 --> 00:05:27.474
How much?

00:05:30.435 --> 00:05:31.561
One million won.

00:05:37.317 --> 00:05:38.568
For real?

00:05:38.652 --> 00:05:39.903
What…

00:05:41.404 --> 00:05:43.531
- Oh yeah!
- One million won!

00:05:49.454 --> 00:05:51.498
Hey, hang on. Quiet!

00:05:51.581 --> 00:05:53.708
Coach, is this for real?

00:05:54.793 --> 00:05:57.504
- Of course it is!
- Yeah!

00:05:58.463 --> 00:06:00.632
Hey! Are you guys ready
to play for real today?

00:06:00.715 --> 00:06:02.050
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:06:02.133 --> 00:06:04.010
- Do you need tactics?
- No!

00:06:04.094 --> 00:06:06.721
- Do we need to analyze the other team?
- No!

00:06:06.805 --> 00:06:08.473
All right, let's go!

00:06:12.435 --> 00:06:14.688
Hey! We're going positionless!

00:06:14.771 --> 00:06:16.982
- Let's do it!
- Show them how it's done!

00:06:19.609 --> 00:06:21.194
DAEHEUNG WINS ANYTIME, ANYWHERE

00:06:21.277 --> 00:06:23.321
Maybe it's because
I heard all that crappy nonsense.

00:06:23.405 --> 00:06:25.991
I can't believe I had
that stupid dream again.

00:06:26.074 --> 00:06:28.660
It's starting to get to me.

00:06:28.743 --> 00:06:29.661
Okay. One, two!

00:06:29.744 --> 00:06:32.497
- Daeheung, Daeheung, let's go!
- Daeheung, Daeheung, let's go!

00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:35.000
- Let's go!
- There's Si-yeol.

00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:44.009
- Suncheon!
- Suncheon!

00:06:45.677 --> 00:06:47.095
- Suncheon!
- Suncheon!

00:06:47.178 --> 00:06:51.099
What's gotten into them today?

00:06:51.182 --> 00:06:53.184
I dangled some money in front of them.

00:06:54.728 --> 00:06:58.356
Look at them. They're full of energy now.

00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:00.984
They're running around like excited mutts.

00:07:03.987 --> 00:07:05.447
- You…
- My bad.

00:07:06.406 --> 00:07:07.615
I forgot to tell you

00:07:08.116 --> 00:07:10.577
that I'm now the owner of that loser club.

00:07:11.786 --> 00:07:12.746
The owner?

00:07:14.914 --> 00:07:15.999
I did some digging,

00:07:16.082 --> 00:07:19.002
and you seem pretty tight
with Kang Si-yeol over there.

00:07:19.919 --> 00:07:23.965
Funnily enough, he and I go way back too.

00:07:24.049 --> 00:07:25.508
I'm sure

00:07:26.801 --> 00:07:28.261
you're already aware of that.

00:07:31.431 --> 00:07:33.308
You're acting pretty cocky today.

00:07:33.391 --> 00:07:37.979
Last time we met,
you couldn't even look me in the eye.

00:07:40.315 --> 00:07:42.442
Not anymore.

00:07:43.026 --> 00:07:44.235
I heard

00:07:44.986 --> 00:07:46.738
you're just an ordinary human now.

00:07:50.158 --> 00:07:54.704
You know, I've got to admit
that I was terrified of you.

00:07:54.788 --> 00:07:58.500
I never knew when you'd show up
or what you'd do,

00:07:58.583 --> 00:08:02.295
so I just hid like a scared little coward.

00:08:02.378 --> 00:08:05.381
Man, that felt…

00:08:07.217 --> 00:08:08.426
like absolute shit.

00:08:10.178 --> 00:08:11.721
What are you plotting?

00:08:11.805 --> 00:08:14.933
I'm just here to let you know
that things have changed.

00:08:20.522 --> 00:08:22.482
You must've enjoyed looking down on us,

00:08:22.565 --> 00:08:25.985
toying with people
like it was all a game to you.

00:08:26.653 --> 00:08:28.321
But now it's my turn.

00:08:28.863 --> 00:08:30.532
Here in the human world,

00:08:30.615 --> 00:08:35.161
I'll show you how hellish life can get
when you cross someone like me.

00:08:36.579 --> 00:08:39.666
Luckily, I still have that much sway.

00:08:45.839 --> 00:08:47.799
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

00:08:49.134 --> 00:08:51.719
Coach, we won a million won!

00:08:51.803 --> 00:08:54.639
A million won! I can't believe this!

00:08:54.722 --> 00:08:56.182
It's a million won!

00:08:56.266 --> 00:08:57.725
- Unbelievable!
- A million won!

00:08:58.601 --> 00:09:01.479
I'm going to start
by targeting the people around you,

00:09:01.563 --> 00:09:03.189
one by one.

00:09:04.023 --> 00:09:04.899
What?

00:09:04.983 --> 00:09:07.944
Where's the fun
in ending things so quickly?

00:09:09.195 --> 00:09:11.406
Now that the tables have turned,

00:09:12.031 --> 00:09:14.742
don't you think it's only fair
for me to toy with you?

00:09:17.996 --> 00:09:19.122
Hey, did you see that?

00:09:19.205 --> 00:09:23.251
I want you to be terrified,
never knowing when I'll strike,

00:09:23.751 --> 00:09:26.963
feeling like shit
for being such a pathetic mess.

00:09:42.812 --> 00:09:43.771
We're going to kill her.

00:09:45.231 --> 00:09:46.482
- Hey!
- What?

00:09:46.566 --> 00:09:48.026
- Hey!
- What's wrong?

00:09:49.569 --> 00:09:50.653
What are you doing, Si-yeol?

00:09:50.737 --> 00:09:52.030
Si-yeol!

00:09:52.113 --> 00:09:54.282
Man, this is fun already.

00:09:55.200 --> 00:09:57.076
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

00:09:58.953 --> 00:10:00.872
- Oh boy.
- What do you want?

00:10:01.581 --> 00:10:03.833
Is this allowed when the game's still on?

00:10:03.917 --> 00:10:07.462
Tell me why you keep
lurking around Eun-ho!

00:10:07.545 --> 00:10:08.838
You know why.

00:10:08.922 --> 00:10:11.341
I have a score to settle with that fox.

00:10:11.424 --> 00:10:12.759
You bastard.

00:10:14.135 --> 00:10:15.386
Oh my God!

00:10:16.137 --> 00:10:18.556
Hey, what the hell
do you think you're doing?

00:10:18.640 --> 00:10:20.225
Man, that hurts.

00:10:20.308 --> 00:10:21.893
Sir, are you okay?

00:10:22.518 --> 00:10:25.104
You really need to control
your players better, Coach.

00:10:25.772 --> 00:10:28.441
He's not an athlete. He's a total thug.

00:10:28.524 --> 00:10:29.442
You little--

00:10:30.526 --> 00:10:32.737
- Hey.
- Come on.

00:10:32.820 --> 00:10:34.072
Oh my. You're bleeding.

00:10:35.782 --> 00:10:37.909
Seriously, what was that?

00:10:38.451 --> 00:10:41.663
We started off strong,
so I thought we'd win.

00:10:41.746 --> 00:10:42.664
Si-yeol!

00:10:42.747 --> 00:10:45.500
Where is he? Where is that bastard?

00:10:45.583 --> 00:10:46.793
- Coach!
- No, Coach!

00:10:46.876 --> 00:10:49.003
- Si-yeol, you…
- Whoa, calm down.

00:10:49.087 --> 00:10:50.463
Si-yeol isn't here.

00:10:50.546 --> 00:10:52.298
- He's not? Okay, fine.
- Si-yeol's gone.

00:10:52.382 --> 00:10:54.384
So where did
that bastard go then?

00:10:55.051 --> 00:10:56.010
Well,

00:10:56.552 --> 00:10:58.805
I think he left early
after getting the red card.

00:11:00.723 --> 00:11:02.058
What? He left?

00:11:02.809 --> 00:11:06.813
Wow, the least he could do is
get on his knees and beg for forgiveness,

00:11:06.896 --> 00:11:08.106
but he just left?

00:11:08.648 --> 00:11:10.483
Seriously, is he nuts?

00:11:10.566 --> 00:11:13.987
I'm sure he left because he felt
too embarrassed to face us--

00:11:14.070 --> 00:11:17.323
Sure! That jerk has it real easy, right?

00:11:17.407 --> 00:11:19.534
He has amazing team spirit.

00:11:19.617 --> 00:11:21.953
Hey, I'm tearing up.
Seriously, I'm so moved.

00:11:23.997 --> 00:11:25.748
But you know what?

00:11:25.832 --> 00:11:29.502
Thanks to Si-yeol, our team is screwed.

00:11:29.585 --> 00:11:30.878
Come on, Coach.

00:11:30.962 --> 00:11:34.132
I mean, Si-yeol did mess up,
but I'm sure it's not that bad.

00:11:34.215 --> 00:11:36.467
We'll do better in our next match.

00:11:36.551 --> 00:11:38.636
Oh, sure.
Just do better in the next match.

00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:43.558
Right. But do you know
who Si-yeol beat up today?

00:11:46.019 --> 00:11:48.187
He was none other than

00:11:49.105 --> 00:11:51.316
our new club owner.

00:11:54.027 --> 00:11:57.864
A member of the family
that owns Geumsu Group!

00:11:57.947 --> 00:12:01.409
Wait, hold on. A billionaire?

00:12:01.492 --> 00:12:05.538
Wait, does that mean our team
is owned by a huge conglomerate?

00:12:05.621 --> 00:12:07.081
Not anymore, you idiot!

00:12:07.165 --> 00:12:10.335
Because of Si-yeol, the deal is off!

00:12:11.669 --> 00:12:14.797
Your 200,000-won match fee

00:12:14.881 --> 00:12:17.508
and the million-won win bonus
are all gone.

00:12:17.592 --> 00:12:21.888
And since we have no sponsor,
our team really is shutting down for good!

00:12:22.472 --> 00:12:24.140
Si-yeol, that bastard!

00:12:24.223 --> 00:12:27.769
He punched the new club owner
right in the face!

00:12:27.852 --> 00:12:29.479
And he landed a direct hit!

00:12:29.562 --> 00:12:32.023
Guys! What am I supposed to do now?

00:12:32.106 --> 00:12:33.566
I'm going to kill…

00:12:33.649 --> 00:12:35.693
- Hey…
- Coach! Your knees!

00:12:35.777 --> 00:12:37.737
Hey! Call 911!

00:12:37.820 --> 00:12:39.864
SUNCHEON STATION

00:12:48.122 --> 00:12:50.625
- Where are we going?
- Straight back to Seoul.

00:12:51.709 --> 00:12:53.461
What's going to change if we leave?

00:12:54.504 --> 00:12:55.963
I know, but…

00:12:56.798 --> 00:12:59.217
You know what kind of guy he is.

00:12:59.300 --> 00:13:01.052
He tried to kill you back then.

00:13:02.261 --> 00:13:03.304
He did.

00:13:03.388 --> 00:13:07.308
When he showed up like that,
you should've run or screamed.

00:13:07.392 --> 00:13:10.436
That's what you should've done.
You're not who you used to be.

00:13:11.104 --> 00:13:12.355
I know that.

00:13:14.065 --> 00:13:16.984
It was so unexpected.
I think I just froze.

00:13:18.611 --> 00:13:22.865
Still, you shouldn't have
run out mid-game.

00:13:22.949 --> 00:13:25.743
It's not like something bad
was going to happen right away.

00:13:27.578 --> 00:13:28.663
Si-yeol.

00:13:33.209 --> 00:13:34.544
I was so scared.

00:13:44.846 --> 00:13:47.348
Seeing him there, right next to you,

00:13:48.933 --> 00:13:52.770
I couldn't think of anything else.
I was just scared.

00:13:53.813 --> 00:13:55.273
Honestly, I still am.

00:13:56.441 --> 00:13:59.026
There's nothing I can do
to protect you right now.

00:13:59.652 --> 00:14:02.196
If he tries
to pull something on you again,

00:14:02.280 --> 00:14:04.949
I don't even know what I should do.

00:14:09.537 --> 00:14:10.705
Don't worry.

00:14:11.747 --> 00:14:13.749
Looks like they found out

00:14:14.375 --> 00:14:18.379
that I became human
and that I'm trying to change back.

00:14:19.255 --> 00:14:22.133
Worst case, I can ask
the eight-tailed fox for help.

00:14:22.758 --> 00:14:24.385
It'll be fine.

00:14:29.891 --> 00:14:31.017
It's okay.

00:14:33.186 --> 00:14:34.395
Sis.

00:14:36.939 --> 00:14:38.816
Can you really not hear me?

00:15:02.507 --> 00:15:04.509
What just happened?

00:15:05.301 --> 00:15:06.677
Wake up.

00:15:14.268 --> 00:15:16.604
Hand over your fox bead.

00:15:16.687 --> 00:15:18.856
I've got a good use for it.

00:15:21.234 --> 00:15:22.735
I'm afraid I can't do that.

00:15:23.986 --> 00:15:25.196
What?

00:15:25.279 --> 00:15:26.948
My fox bead

00:15:28.324 --> 00:15:29.825
isn't on me right now.

00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:34.455
Seriously, what do I do?

00:15:35.540 --> 00:15:38.793
I already told him where my fox bead is.

00:15:40.294 --> 00:15:43.673
And I can't even warn her to be careful.

00:15:43.756 --> 00:15:46.467
Let's move as soon as we get to Seoul.

00:15:47.343 --> 00:15:49.720
It's way too cramped
and uncomfortable anyway.

00:15:50.346 --> 00:15:53.599
And then, we'll get you
back to normal as soon as…

00:15:54.100 --> 00:15:55.643
- Wait a second.
- Yeah?

00:15:56.185 --> 00:15:59.772
Have you always had that sweater?

00:16:00.565 --> 00:16:01.732
You mean this?

00:16:02.400 --> 00:16:05.861
I found it while packing. Is it weird?

00:16:06.404 --> 00:16:08.072
No, it's just…

00:16:09.156 --> 00:16:10.992
I've just never seen it before.

00:16:11.075 --> 00:16:14.036
I've had this for a really long time.

00:16:14.120 --> 00:16:15.580
My grandma bought it for me.

00:16:23.379 --> 00:16:25.506
So it wasn't a dream.

00:16:26.841 --> 00:16:32.096
It's a future I can't change or avoid.

00:16:32.179 --> 00:16:34.432
Are you telling me to choose?

00:16:34.515 --> 00:16:38.936
Kill Si-yeol, or give up who I am?

00:16:39.562 --> 00:16:41.272
It may seem cruel,

00:16:41.355 --> 00:16:43.899
but fate simply takes its course.

00:16:43.983 --> 00:16:47.486
It does not concern itself
with individual human affairs.

00:16:47.570 --> 00:16:51.657
Once the storm rises,
everyone gets swept away.

00:16:51.741 --> 00:16:55.870
Can you truly handle that for a lifetime?

00:16:58.289 --> 00:16:59.540
Si-yeol.

00:16:59.624 --> 00:17:02.918
What exactly are we being swept up in

00:17:03.919 --> 00:17:06.255
to face a future like that?

00:17:08.966 --> 00:17:11.260
Why would you…

00:17:13.846 --> 00:17:14.889
Si-yeol.

00:17:15.890 --> 00:17:17.141
I can't do this.

00:17:18.643 --> 00:17:20.811
- What?
- I've been thinking…

00:17:22.688 --> 00:17:24.940
and I don't want to just leave like this.

00:17:25.024 --> 00:17:26.442
We came here for a trip.

00:17:26.525 --> 00:17:29.153
I don't want to just run away
like we're being chased.

00:17:30.321 --> 00:17:31.656
Let's get off this train.

00:17:36.077 --> 00:17:39.622
They say this village has been here
since the Joseon Dynasty.

00:17:40.164 --> 00:17:43.292
Even these thatched houses
are hundreds of years old--

00:17:43.376 --> 00:17:45.461
Did you forget who I am?

00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:47.338
What?

00:17:47.421 --> 00:17:50.424
I used to live in places like this
back in the day.

00:17:50.508 --> 00:17:55.012
You call this a tourist spot?
It's just a regular village.

00:17:55.930 --> 00:17:58.015
Oh, right.

00:18:00.768 --> 00:18:04.480
I saw that this was a famous tourist spot
around here.

00:18:05.356 --> 00:18:08.776
- Should we go somewhere else?
- No, we came all this way.

00:18:09.318 --> 00:18:12.029
Come on, let's look around.

00:18:13.948 --> 00:18:15.032
Oh man…

00:18:31.215 --> 00:18:32.216
Si-yeol.

00:18:32.967 --> 00:18:35.261
Give the roof a little shake
with that stick.

00:18:35.344 --> 00:18:37.596
The roof? Why?

00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:39.140
To make the grubs fall down.

00:18:39.849 --> 00:18:43.561
They should be nice and plump
right about now.

00:18:43.644 --> 00:18:47.857
What? Aren't grubs bugs?
What would you need them for?

00:18:47.940 --> 00:18:50.443
Since we're here,
you should try them as a snack.

00:18:51.235 --> 00:18:53.446
No way. What are you talking about?

00:18:53.529 --> 00:18:55.698
Try it. Do you want me to catch one?

00:18:56.365 --> 00:18:58.409
You don't have to. I said no.

00:18:58.492 --> 00:19:00.035
They taste better than you think.

00:19:00.119 --> 00:19:03.622
Back in the day, old folks used to use
grubs as medicine, you know?

00:19:03.706 --> 00:19:06.000
- I'll catch one for you.
- Wait…

00:19:08.753 --> 00:19:10.129
What…

00:19:15.092 --> 00:19:16.594
Hey, don't. Don't do it!

00:19:16.677 --> 00:19:19.513
- Why? I'll get you a grub.
- Forget the grub.

00:19:19.597 --> 00:19:22.224
But we came all this way.
You have to try it.

00:19:22.308 --> 00:19:24.393
Wait, just put it down. Seriously.

00:19:24.477 --> 00:19:26.604
Come on, you should have a taste.

00:19:26.687 --> 00:19:27.772
Hey, I'm not eating it!

00:19:27.855 --> 00:19:28.898
SAMSHIN

00:19:28.981 --> 00:19:32.401
Samshin. Like this.

00:19:34.069 --> 00:19:35.738
Do this one too.

00:19:35.821 --> 00:19:37.198
- I'm not doing it anymore.
- Come on.

00:19:37.281 --> 00:19:39.366
Forget it, I'm done.

00:19:39.450 --> 00:19:40.326
I'm not doing it.

00:19:44.038 --> 00:19:46.791
- Here, lie down.
- What? No way.

00:19:46.874 --> 00:19:50.586
- Please lie down, just once.
- No, let's just look around and go.

00:19:51.212 --> 00:19:53.506
Come on, just lie down once.

00:19:53.589 --> 00:19:55.424
- Please?
- No. You're going to hit me.

00:19:55.508 --> 00:19:56.675
No, wait.

00:19:56.759 --> 00:19:57.635
Hey!

00:20:07.311 --> 00:20:08.854
- What?
- Nice!

00:20:08.938 --> 00:20:10.606
- Give me your palm.
- No. Let's do it again.

00:20:10.689 --> 00:20:12.399
- Come on, give me your wrist.
- No!

00:20:13.067 --> 00:20:15.444
Hey, what are you doing?
You can't throw it like that!

00:20:15.528 --> 00:20:17.404
Oh my. Look at this.

00:20:18.364 --> 00:20:20.491
Wow, look at this place.

00:20:21.992 --> 00:20:23.661
Si-yeol, do you know what this is?

00:20:23.744 --> 00:20:26.372
- What is it?
- It's cotton.

00:20:26.455 --> 00:20:28.582
Do you know how to make clothes out of it?

00:20:28.666 --> 00:20:30.626
First, you take out the cotton seeds.

00:20:30.709 --> 00:20:33.546
You take out the seed, and then there's
something called a cotton bow.

00:20:33.629 --> 00:20:36.841
And if you beat the seeds with that,
it puffs up like cotton.

00:20:36.924 --> 00:20:40.761
Then you take a handful of it,
put it on a sorghum stalk, and spin it…

00:20:45.099 --> 00:20:47.351
Here you go.

00:20:57.862 --> 00:20:58.904
Open wide.

00:21:02.533 --> 00:21:03.993
Mm! It's good.

00:21:11.083 --> 00:21:13.961
- It's good, right?
- It's even better because you fed me.

00:21:14.044 --> 00:21:15.296
Gosh, stop it.

00:21:48.621 --> 00:21:49.872
What's with the sudden photo?

00:21:51.040 --> 00:21:53.542
Oh, I just thought you looked pretty.

00:21:54.376 --> 00:21:55.377
Gosh.

00:21:57.922 --> 00:22:00.591
Take it again. I wasn't ready.

00:22:04.094 --> 00:22:05.012
You look so pretty.

00:22:07.848 --> 00:22:09.808
It came out well. Let me show you.

00:22:13.103 --> 00:22:14.897
It did come out well!

00:22:19.777 --> 00:22:22.446
You should stand here too.
This looks like a good photo spot.

00:22:22.529 --> 00:22:24.740
Actually, why don't we take one together?

00:22:24.823 --> 00:22:26.992
- What?
- Come to think of it,

00:22:27.076 --> 00:22:29.119
we don't have any photos together.

00:22:31.664 --> 00:22:32.665
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

00:22:32.748 --> 00:22:34.917
- Could you take a photo of us?
- Sure.

00:22:37.461 --> 00:22:38.712
Are you ready?

00:22:39.380 --> 00:22:41.382
One, two, three.

00:22:51.225 --> 00:22:53.143
Oh, jeez!

00:22:53.644 --> 00:22:55.604
You scared the hell out of me.

00:22:55.688 --> 00:22:56.647
Seriously.

00:22:57.147 --> 00:23:00.484
You can't just walk in here. Damn it.

00:23:03.612 --> 00:23:04.613
What is it?

00:23:05.656 --> 00:23:08.826
You look like you're already
halfway to the grave.

00:23:11.245 --> 00:23:14.581
Catching that other fox
must've been tough on you.

00:23:14.665 --> 00:23:15.749
Not yet.

00:23:16.834 --> 00:23:19.420
- What?
- I said it's not over.

00:23:19.503 --> 00:23:21.130
I couldn't get the fox bead.

00:23:22.214 --> 00:23:23.590
What are you talking about?

00:23:24.508 --> 00:23:26.719
Then nothing's changed at all.

00:23:26.802 --> 00:23:28.178
Jeez.

00:23:29.680 --> 00:23:33.058
I went to that former nine-tailed fox
and made all sorts of threats.

00:23:33.142 --> 00:23:37.187
If that other monster is still with her,
what am I supposed to do now?

00:23:38.063 --> 00:23:40.149
No need to get so worked up.

00:23:40.691 --> 00:23:44.445
How can I not get worked up?

00:23:44.528 --> 00:23:46.530
You took two billion won from me.

00:23:47.614 --> 00:23:52.578
If that other fox is still with her,
do you really think she'll let me be?

00:23:53.662 --> 00:23:55.164
You really are a coward.

00:23:56.790 --> 00:23:59.835
I bewitched the Seoraksan Mountain fox,
just as planned.

00:23:59.918 --> 00:24:01.420
But in exchange,

00:24:02.046 --> 00:24:03.839
I burned up all my shamanic power

00:24:04.798 --> 00:24:07.342
when I already don't have much time left.

00:24:08.010 --> 00:24:10.554
So what's going to happen now?

00:24:10.637 --> 00:24:12.473
I'll be dead soon,

00:24:12.556 --> 00:24:15.476
unless I find and swallow that fox bead
in the next few days.

00:24:17.436 --> 00:24:19.855
That's your problem. But what about me?

00:24:20.606 --> 00:24:21.940
What's going to happen to me?

00:24:23.692 --> 00:24:25.778
Figure that one out yourself, you punk.

00:24:27.488 --> 00:24:31.408
But if you're scared of that fox
sticking around her,

00:24:31.492 --> 00:24:33.619
you don't need to worry
about that anymore.

00:24:34.161 --> 00:24:36.997
She's just a puppet now,
and she can only do what I tell her.

00:24:37.081 --> 00:24:39.333
She'll stay that way until I die.

00:24:40.793 --> 00:24:43.837
Really? Are you sure
I don't have to worry about it?

00:24:44.463 --> 00:24:48.300
Yes. I ordered her
to go fetch the fox bead herself.

00:24:48.383 --> 00:24:50.094
You can see for yourself then…

00:24:51.220 --> 00:24:54.348
whether that fox does
what I tell her to do or not.

00:25:10.405 --> 00:25:11.448
This is nice.

00:25:12.407 --> 00:25:13.700
I'm glad.

00:25:14.243 --> 00:25:16.411
I thought today's trip was a total bust

00:25:16.995 --> 00:25:19.039
because I took you to a Joseon-era village

00:25:19.123 --> 00:25:20.874
when you lived through that era.

00:25:22.626 --> 00:25:25.003
Walking through that old village with you

00:25:25.671 --> 00:25:29.925
made me feel
like we've known each other forever.

00:25:30.801 --> 00:25:32.010
I liked that.

00:25:34.096 --> 00:25:37.015
It felt like you became
a small part of all those years

00:25:37.599 --> 00:25:39.977
I spent alone in my past.

00:25:41.937 --> 00:25:45.149
Next time, let's go somewhere better.
Somewhere you've never been.

00:25:45.816 --> 00:25:50.946
Then I can be part of your past
and your future, right?

00:25:51.029 --> 00:25:54.867
Yeah. That'd be really nice.

00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:04.001
Si-yeol.

00:26:07.087 --> 00:26:08.380
Should we just…

00:26:10.174 --> 00:26:13.552
stay like this and not go back?

00:26:14.178 --> 00:26:15.053
What?

00:26:15.137 --> 00:26:17.055
I could just be an ordinary human.

00:26:17.139 --> 00:26:20.642
And instead of being the famous
Kang Si-yeol that everyone knows,

00:26:22.060 --> 00:26:25.105
you'd stay a fourth-division player,
just like now.

00:26:34.865 --> 00:26:35.741
Hey.

00:26:35.824 --> 00:26:37.576
I was just joking,

00:26:38.118 --> 00:26:42.122
but you went all quiet,
and now it feels way too serious.

00:26:44.208 --> 00:26:46.001
Okay. Let's do it.

00:26:49.546 --> 00:26:50.547
What?

00:26:50.631 --> 00:26:53.217
If that's what you want, let's do it.

00:26:56.011 --> 00:26:58.889
Are you really okay living like this?

00:27:00.015 --> 00:27:02.392
Your dreams, your hard work,
and everything you've achieved

00:27:02.476 --> 00:27:04.102
are not part of this life.

00:27:04.186 --> 00:27:05.896
How can you be okay with that?

00:27:05.979 --> 00:27:07.606
And you saw what happened earlier.

00:27:07.689 --> 00:27:11.068
People with a grudge against me
are coming after you too.

00:27:11.151 --> 00:27:14.696
If we stay like this,
it won't be a normal life.

00:27:15.948 --> 00:27:18.659
We might have to spend our lives
looking over our shoulders.

00:27:20.619 --> 00:27:22.663
I'm not saying it would be okay.

00:27:22.746 --> 00:27:25.165
I'm saying I'm okay with it not being okay

00:27:27.668 --> 00:27:29.169
What does that even--

00:27:29.253 --> 00:27:31.505
I know you're hiding something from me.

00:27:32.923 --> 00:27:36.176
Ever since we came back
from visiting Woo-seok at the hospital,

00:27:36.260 --> 00:27:37.719
you've been acting weird.

00:27:38.804 --> 00:27:40.222
I don't know what it is,

00:27:40.847 --> 00:27:41.932
but knowing you,

00:27:42.015 --> 00:27:44.643
you'd have told me already
if it wasn't a big deal.

00:27:44.726 --> 00:27:47.479
You're struggling alone,
and you can't even tell me,

00:27:48.355 --> 00:27:50.524
so it must be a problem we can't solve.

00:27:52.067 --> 00:27:53.151
Si-yeol…

00:27:53.235 --> 00:27:55.279
If it's a matter of choice,

00:27:56.280 --> 00:27:58.699
of course I want to go back
to how things were.

00:27:59.491 --> 00:28:04.454
Like you said, my life, my hard work,
the dreams that I achieved

00:28:05.747 --> 00:28:07.416
all mean a great deal to me.

00:28:08.542 --> 00:28:09.584
However,

00:28:10.585 --> 00:28:12.337
if you try your best

00:28:12.421 --> 00:28:15.424
to change things back and still can't,

00:28:16.466 --> 00:28:17.718
it's okay.

00:28:18.343 --> 00:28:19.636
I'll just accept it.

00:28:24.141 --> 00:28:27.102
It's not over yet, and I haven't given up.

00:28:27.853 --> 00:28:33.233
I'll keep trying to find the best solution
for both of us until the very last moment.

00:28:35.027 --> 00:28:36.028
I know.

00:28:42.284 --> 00:28:44.286
But I'm scared.

00:28:45.829 --> 00:28:48.040
I'm scared that we'll get swept away

00:28:49.124 --> 00:28:51.084
by fate or that damn will of Heaven.

00:28:53.086 --> 00:28:54.171
I'm scared…

00:28:56.173 --> 00:28:58.342
that I won't be able to protect us.

00:29:01.720 --> 00:29:03.055
Si-yeol,

00:29:04.348 --> 00:29:05.474
I think…

00:29:08.352 --> 00:29:10.812
I really like you.

00:29:54.022 --> 00:29:55.232
What?

00:29:57.651 --> 00:30:00.654
I specifically asked for twin beds,

00:30:01.279 --> 00:30:02.823
but it's a double.

00:30:09.746 --> 00:30:12.499
Maybe we should've
just gone back to Seoul.

00:30:12.582 --> 00:30:14.793
Yeah, maybe.

00:30:17.254 --> 00:30:19.840
But then again, we are on a trip.

00:30:20.757 --> 00:30:22.926
Right. And it's late.

00:30:23.552 --> 00:30:27.222
- And we're tired from all the walking.
- Yeah, that's right.

00:30:27.305 --> 00:30:28.807
Yeah.

00:30:31.435 --> 00:30:34.354
Do you want to look around?

00:30:35.814 --> 00:30:36.773
Sure.

00:30:37.274 --> 00:30:40.068
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:30:43.905 --> 00:30:45.198
Here, give me that.

00:30:45.740 --> 00:30:48.160
Yeah, okay.

00:31:00.255 --> 00:31:01.298
Hey,

00:31:01.381 --> 00:31:03.216
we've been living in the same house.

00:31:03.300 --> 00:31:05.469
Why are you being so awkward?

00:31:06.553 --> 00:31:09.055
Who, me? I'm not being awkward.

00:31:10.307 --> 00:31:11.975
Seriously, I'm not.

00:31:12.809 --> 00:31:13.935
Maybe you're feeling awkward.

00:31:16.563 --> 00:31:18.899
Not at all. I don't feel awkward.

00:31:32.662 --> 00:31:33.663
Oh, right.

00:31:34.331 --> 00:31:36.416
I should ask them to switch rooms.

00:31:45.300 --> 00:31:46.301
It's fine.

00:31:48.053 --> 00:31:49.095
What?

00:31:49.721 --> 00:31:52.516
I mean, this room is actually really nice.

00:31:55.977 --> 00:31:58.104
It's got an ocean view and everything.

00:32:01.024 --> 00:32:03.902
So, you don't have to go ask.

00:32:12.661 --> 00:32:13.828
You told me not to, okay?

00:32:16.665 --> 00:32:17.707
What?

00:33:06.464 --> 00:33:07.591
I love you.

00:33:52.093 --> 00:33:54.179
- Are you awake?
- Yeah.

00:33:54.721 --> 00:33:55.764
When did you wake up?

00:33:56.640 --> 00:33:57.724
Just now.

00:34:02.729 --> 00:34:05.732
- Do you want to sleep a bit longer?
- Yeah, just a little.

00:34:13.907 --> 00:34:15.075
But seriously…

00:34:16.117 --> 00:34:17.494
I just don't get him.

00:34:17.577 --> 00:34:21.164
He's a lunatic. Why did he have to
drag us down with him?

00:34:25.669 --> 00:34:29.047
And why is he skipping training
like he's done nothing wrong?

00:34:30.423 --> 00:34:31.841
Forget all that.

00:34:32.342 --> 00:34:34.803
Is there even any point
in training like this?

00:34:34.886 --> 00:34:37.430
Most of us can't even transfer anywhere.

00:34:37.514 --> 00:34:39.265
We're all just
going to be forced to retire.

00:34:39.349 --> 00:34:43.395
I knew Si-yeol
would eventually mess up big time.

00:34:43.478 --> 00:34:44.938
Man, I'm tired.

00:34:45.021 --> 00:34:48.233
I was so stressed that
I couldn't get a wink of sleep last night.

00:34:52.362 --> 00:34:54.072
- Want one?
- Thanks.

00:34:54.698 --> 00:34:55.990
Give me one too.

00:34:58.410 --> 00:34:59.619
It's kicking in now.

00:35:00.829 --> 00:35:02.789
Man, caffeine really helps.

00:35:02.872 --> 00:35:04.624
I'm done with Si-yeol.

00:35:05.875 --> 00:35:07.335
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

00:35:07.961 --> 00:35:11.047
I mean, if he messed up that badly,

00:35:11.131 --> 00:35:13.007
he should be begging
the owner for forgiveness.

00:35:13.091 --> 00:35:14.426
Or at least try to fix it.

00:35:14.509 --> 00:35:16.928
How can he ghost us instead?
I'm so pissed off.

00:35:19.556 --> 00:35:21.307
Should I try calling him or something?

00:35:21.391 --> 00:35:22.642
Forget it. Don't bother.

00:35:23.935 --> 00:35:25.311
Excuse me. Is the coach in?

00:35:25.395 --> 00:35:27.605
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:35:28.481 --> 00:35:29.983
Coach didn't come in today.

00:35:30.650 --> 00:35:32.694
Oh, really?

00:35:32.777 --> 00:35:33.987
What brings you here?

00:35:34.070 --> 00:35:35.697
Well, it's just…

00:35:36.197 --> 00:35:39.492
I think I know why Si-yeol
acted the way he did yesterday.

00:35:39.576 --> 00:35:41.828
I think I might have made a mistake.

00:35:41.911 --> 00:35:44.998
I can't believe
that I completely forgot about that.

00:35:45.915 --> 00:35:48.001
What do you mean?

00:35:49.794 --> 00:35:53.047
Are you sure
you don't need to go to training?

00:35:53.131 --> 00:35:55.341
How could I go anywhere
and leave you alone?

00:35:55.425 --> 00:35:58.011
I'm not leaving your side for a while.

00:35:58.511 --> 00:36:00.305
Jeez, I'm not a child.

00:36:01.347 --> 00:36:03.141
It's for the best, actually.

00:36:03.224 --> 00:36:06.019
Honestly, we don't have time
to be distracted by training and stuff.

00:36:06.102 --> 00:36:08.271
We need to find
the people you listed in your notebook,

00:36:08.354 --> 00:36:11.024
and find out where they are
and what they're doing.

00:36:11.357 --> 00:36:12.400
You're right.

00:36:14.235 --> 00:36:15.278
Oh, wait.

00:36:16.321 --> 00:36:17.822
You know that sweater from yesterday?

00:36:17.906 --> 00:36:19.783
- Yeah.
- Do you have it right now?

00:36:21.117 --> 00:36:22.660
Let's throw it away over there.

00:36:22.744 --> 00:36:24.913
What are you talking about?

00:36:24.996 --> 00:36:27.040
I told you my grandma bought me that.

00:36:27.123 --> 00:36:29.334
Is that the only thing
she ever bought you?

00:36:30.043 --> 00:36:31.836
No, I have a lot, but--

00:36:31.920 --> 00:36:35.673
Then throw it away. It looks weird,
and the color's wrong for you.

00:36:35.757 --> 00:36:37.175
Really, it doesn't suit you.

00:36:37.258 --> 00:36:40.553
What do you mean? It looks good on me.

00:36:44.641 --> 00:36:45.642
Throw it away.

00:36:48.102 --> 00:36:50.104
But it's perfectly fine.

00:36:51.147 --> 00:36:53.024
I really like this sweater.

00:36:53.733 --> 00:36:56.110
Well, I totally hate it.

00:36:58.279 --> 00:36:59.739
Should I throw it away?

00:37:00.782 --> 00:37:03.576
Man, that temper of yours. Fine.

00:37:08.832 --> 00:37:10.583
I was on edge all day yesterday,

00:37:10.667 --> 00:37:13.086
thinking something
would happen at any second.

00:37:13.169 --> 00:37:14.629
I should've done this sooner.

00:37:15.129 --> 00:37:16.422
What?

00:37:17.131 --> 00:37:18.132
Nothing.

00:37:30.186 --> 00:37:33.189
Why did we come all the way here?
He'll come out when he's ready.

00:37:33.273 --> 00:37:36.776
Come on, stop acting all tough
and just come along.

00:37:36.860 --> 00:37:38.736
We're already here anyway.

00:37:38.820 --> 00:37:41.823
Si-yeol should've told us that earlier.

00:37:41.906 --> 00:37:43.658
I would've lost it too

00:37:43.741 --> 00:37:47.787
if the guy who ruined my life
in a hit-and-run suddenly showed up.

00:37:48.413 --> 00:37:50.373
I looked him up on our way here.

00:37:50.456 --> 00:37:52.667
Turns out he's a murderer,
a total scumbag.

00:37:53.209 --> 00:37:56.963
We don't want a person like that
as our club owner, either.

00:37:57.046 --> 00:37:59.716
- Yeah.
- Si-yeol did the right thing this time.

00:38:01.259 --> 00:38:02.468
Si-yeol!

00:38:03.094 --> 00:38:04.345
Hey, Si-yeol!

00:38:05.305 --> 00:38:06.431
I don't think he's home.

00:38:06.514 --> 00:38:08.099
- Damn it.
- Man, it's cold.

00:38:08.182 --> 00:38:09.767
Let's just wait inside.

00:38:18.151 --> 00:38:19.152
What the heck?

00:38:20.069 --> 00:38:21.112
What happened?

00:38:22.572 --> 00:38:23.823
Hey.

00:38:25.783 --> 00:38:28.202
Looks like he really got robbed this time.

00:38:28.828 --> 00:38:32.165
Why are you standing out here?
You could've waited at home.

00:38:33.499 --> 00:38:34.667
Sis.

00:38:35.293 --> 00:38:36.544
Yeah?

00:38:36.628 --> 00:38:38.671
Give my fox bead back.

00:38:48.056 --> 00:38:49.015
Who are you?

00:38:50.642 --> 00:38:51.643
What?

00:39:06.282 --> 00:39:07.367
Wait.

00:39:07.450 --> 00:39:09.118
What do you think you're--

00:39:19.087 --> 00:39:20.755
Where is my fox bead?

00:39:21.422 --> 00:39:24.634
It wasn't at the house,
and you don't seem to have it on you.

00:39:24.717 --> 00:39:25.927
Where did you hide it?

00:39:26.010 --> 00:39:29.138
What if I give it to you?
Who are you offering it to?

00:39:29.764 --> 00:39:31.641
Don't you know what'll happen to you then?

00:39:31.724 --> 00:39:33.017
It's mine.

00:39:33.518 --> 00:39:36.270
However I use it is up to me.

00:39:36.354 --> 00:39:37.730
Snap out of it.

00:39:38.398 --> 00:39:40.066
Did you forget what I told you?

00:39:41.275 --> 00:39:44.904
I don't know what that damn shaman did,

00:39:44.988 --> 00:39:47.240
but you're just an empty shell,
and the real you is gone--

00:39:47.323 --> 00:39:48.700
I guess I have no choice.

00:39:48.783 --> 00:39:51.619
For some reason,
I can't even feel the bead's energy.

00:39:51.703 --> 00:39:53.913
And it seems like you won't just tell me…

00:39:55.873 --> 00:39:57.834
so I'll have to find out for myself.

00:40:14.851 --> 00:40:16.644
What are you staring at?

00:40:18.187 --> 00:40:19.397
Your family.

00:40:20.481 --> 00:40:23.276
Family? Way to kill the mood.

00:40:25.486 --> 00:40:28.197
Anyway, how much longer do I have to wait?

00:40:29.032 --> 00:40:30.116
It won't be long.

00:40:30.199 --> 00:40:33.745
I doubt I'll have any time left
after tonight anyway.

00:40:34.579 --> 00:40:36.289
You might not know this,

00:40:37.790 --> 00:40:39.208
but in here,

00:40:40.126 --> 00:40:44.130
there are all sorts of minor spirits
that hold a grudge against me.

00:40:45.715 --> 00:40:50.261
They're just waiting for me to die
so they can rip my soul to pieces.

00:40:51.345 --> 00:40:52.889
Why say things like that

00:40:52.972 --> 00:40:56.017
to someone living a normal life,
unaware of such things?

00:40:56.768 --> 00:40:59.062
I used to live blissfully unaware too.

00:41:02.732 --> 00:41:04.525
If you get that fox bead,

00:41:05.234 --> 00:41:07.612
does that mean you won't die today?

00:41:08.780 --> 00:41:09.864
No.

00:41:11.449 --> 00:41:12.742
It's more than that.

00:41:13.284 --> 00:41:15.161
I'll become immortal.

00:41:15.995 --> 00:41:16.954
What do you mean…

00:41:18.998 --> 00:41:20.333
I'm going to become a deity.

00:41:20.958 --> 00:41:21.834
What?

00:41:21.918 --> 00:41:26.005
Spiritual beings like the nine-tailed fox
are like demigods, not mere animals.

00:41:26.089 --> 00:41:29.675
So if I steal their fox bead
and swallow it,

00:41:30.510 --> 00:41:33.805
I can shed this human form
and become a deity.

00:41:35.807 --> 00:41:39.310
So? What's your plan
after becoming immortal?

00:41:40.269 --> 00:41:41.229
Revenge.

00:41:42.188 --> 00:41:44.649
You must know roughly
what happened to my family,

00:41:44.732 --> 00:41:46.734
since you did some digging on me.

00:41:47.693 --> 00:41:48.569
Yeah, roughly.

00:41:49.612 --> 00:41:51.280
Just that you refused
the shamanic calling,

00:41:51.364 --> 00:41:53.491
and that's why your whole family
ended up that way.

00:41:53.574 --> 00:41:57.578
At least my wife died quickly.
It was a car accident.

00:41:57.662 --> 00:41:59.664
I was the one behind the wheel,

00:41:59.747 --> 00:42:02.667
and I slammed
right into an oncoming truck.

00:42:02.750 --> 00:42:04.919
It was like I was possessed.

00:42:05.002 --> 00:42:07.255
I didn't have control over my body.

00:42:09.632 --> 00:42:11.425
The car was completely destroyed.

00:42:11.509 --> 00:42:14.804
My wife was torn to pieces
right there on impact.

00:42:14.887 --> 00:42:19.392
But I was in the driver's seat
and didn't have a single scratch on me.

00:42:19.475 --> 00:42:22.436
Since I was their vessel,
they needed me unharmed.

00:42:23.521 --> 00:42:25.773
So you finally accepted
the shamanic calling?

00:42:25.857 --> 00:42:27.024
No.

00:42:28.776 --> 00:42:31.487
Even then,
I cared more about my own life.

00:42:32.238 --> 00:42:34.448
So they went after my daughter.

00:42:36.993 --> 00:42:38.661
It started out of nowhere.

00:42:38.744 --> 00:42:41.747
She was in so much pain,
like she was dying.

00:42:42.498 --> 00:42:44.876
But the doctors couldn't find a cause.

00:42:46.919 --> 00:42:51.090
I was desperate to save her,
so I tried everything and went everywhere.

00:42:51.924 --> 00:42:53.926
Then, she just couldn't take it anymore.

00:42:55.011 --> 00:42:58.222
She took her own life
because she wanted the pain to stop.

00:42:58.973 --> 00:43:02.727
Is it even possible to get revenge
on those beings?

00:43:03.936 --> 00:43:07.565
Of course. Starting with the deity
that did this to us,

00:43:07.648 --> 00:43:11.194
I devoured all sorts of minor spirits.

00:43:11.277 --> 00:43:14.363
It took me years,
but I hunted them down, one by one.

00:43:15.364 --> 00:43:16.782
These marks are the seals.

00:43:19.076 --> 00:43:21.871
They don't control me anymore.

00:43:22.371 --> 00:43:24.707
I'm the one who controls them.

00:43:25.499 --> 00:43:29.253
Wait. Then you already got your revenge.

00:43:29.337 --> 00:43:32.048
No. This isn't just about
these minor spirits.

00:43:32.673 --> 00:43:36.510
I'm talking about the greater deities
who created a world like this, and…

00:43:38.137 --> 00:43:41.849
even this damn world itself.
I'll destroy them all.

00:43:42.475 --> 00:43:44.101
I'll live 100 or 1,000 years if necessary.

00:43:44.185 --> 00:43:47.730
And if even that isn't enough,
I'll live 10,000 years to see it through.

00:44:05.581 --> 00:44:06.958
How is this…

00:44:21.639 --> 00:44:23.474
How did I get home?

00:44:25.643 --> 00:44:27.561
I was just…

00:44:31.857 --> 00:44:33.693
What was I doing again?

00:44:54.797 --> 00:44:56.132
Eun-ho!

00:45:01.012 --> 00:45:02.138
Geum-ho?

00:45:02.221 --> 00:45:05.099
Shopping just isn't fun without you.

00:45:06.559 --> 00:45:09.645
We could've grabbed lunch and some coffee.

00:45:09.729 --> 00:45:11.397
You really should've come along.

00:45:12.023 --> 00:45:13.774
What were you doing here all alone?

00:45:15.234 --> 00:45:16.235
Well,

00:45:17.069 --> 00:45:18.654
I was just…

00:45:22.074 --> 00:45:23.117
But, Geum-ho…

00:45:24.744 --> 00:45:25.786
is it really you?

00:45:27.413 --> 00:45:29.623
- What?
- I mean, I swear

00:45:29.707 --> 00:45:32.501
you became human centuries ago.

00:45:32.585 --> 00:45:34.420
And you got married,

00:45:35.421 --> 00:45:36.589
then…

00:45:38.549 --> 00:45:39.675
you died.

00:45:40.343 --> 00:45:42.678
What are you talking about?
Did you have a dream?

00:45:44.680 --> 00:45:45.681
A dream?

00:45:45.765 --> 00:45:47.350
Forget about that.

00:45:49.477 --> 00:45:50.561
Here, try this on.

00:45:51.187 --> 00:45:53.856
I bought it because I thought
it'd look good on you.

00:46:01.572 --> 00:46:03.240
It must've been a dream.

00:46:04.533 --> 00:46:06.494
Come on. You're not a child.

00:46:07.286 --> 00:46:09.163
What kind of dream was it?

00:46:11.207 --> 00:46:12.500
I'm not really sure.

00:46:13.376 --> 00:46:15.753
It felt so vivid, so real.

00:46:15.836 --> 00:46:18.130
But now that I'm awake,
I can't remember much.

00:46:19.965 --> 00:46:21.550
Just that you weren't with me

00:46:22.259 --> 00:46:25.096
and I was alone for a very long time.

00:46:26.931 --> 00:46:29.141
I think there was someone else too.

00:46:31.102 --> 00:46:33.479
It was just a silly dream. Let's eat.

00:46:33.562 --> 00:46:35.398
I picked up some takeout for us.

00:46:38.609 --> 00:46:40.528
I mean, it was a really strange dream.

00:46:40.611 --> 00:46:45.032
I became a human,
and I think I even dated a man.

00:46:46.117 --> 00:46:48.119
You dated a human?

00:46:48.661 --> 00:46:50.704
What kind of guy was he?

00:46:51.705 --> 00:46:54.041
I don't know. I can't remember that part.

00:46:56.335 --> 00:46:57.837
Was he handsome?

00:46:58.629 --> 00:47:02.091
His face was so clear in the dream,

00:47:02.174 --> 00:47:03.843
but now I can't really recall.

00:47:03.926 --> 00:47:05.094
By the way, Eun-ho.

00:47:05.177 --> 00:47:08.222
You know the thing I left with you?
Where is it?

00:47:09.098 --> 00:47:10.057
What?

00:47:10.141 --> 00:47:11.725
My fox bead.

00:47:13.018 --> 00:47:14.186
You have it.

00:47:18.190 --> 00:47:20.109
Why would I have that?

00:47:21.402 --> 00:47:23.362
Wait, do I?

00:47:26.407 --> 00:47:28.284
Where did I put it?

00:47:30.953 --> 00:47:31.996
Think carefully.

00:47:42.548 --> 00:47:43.966
This place is…

00:47:44.758 --> 00:47:47.720
So, my bead is here?

00:47:49.722 --> 00:47:53.350
Yeah. Why did I keep it here again?

00:47:56.353 --> 00:47:58.898
Oh, right. It was because…

00:47:59.565 --> 00:48:00.733
Sis, snap out of it.

00:48:01.567 --> 00:48:04.278
Don't tell her anything. This is all fake.

00:48:04.945 --> 00:48:05.946
"Sis"?

00:48:06.822 --> 00:48:09.658
Wait, she's not Geum-ho?

00:48:10.409 --> 00:48:13.454
Eun-ho, don't overthink it.

00:48:13.537 --> 00:48:16.540
Just tell me where you hid the fox bead--

00:48:16.624 --> 00:48:18.125
Sis, can't you hear that voice?

00:48:18.918 --> 00:48:19.919
A voice?

00:48:21.504 --> 00:48:24.757
Eun-ho, wake up!

00:48:25.758 --> 00:48:27.092
Eun-ho.

00:48:27.176 --> 00:48:28.636
- Eun-ho.
- Si-yeol?

00:48:29.261 --> 00:48:31.514
Eun-ho, come on. Wake up.

00:48:32.181 --> 00:48:34.183
I was almost there. What a hassle.

00:48:43.192 --> 00:48:45.402
Tell me where you're keeping my fox bead.

00:48:47.696 --> 00:48:49.281
It wasn't in that hospital room.

00:48:50.741 --> 00:48:51.867
Geum-ho.

00:48:55.996 --> 00:49:00.209
So you're saying
there are weird humans after my fox bead?

00:49:00.292 --> 00:49:03.254
Yeah, I heard it from Si-yeol's friend.

00:49:04.129 --> 00:49:07.550
Now that they know I'm human,
I think they're looking for you.

00:49:07.633 --> 00:49:11.095
But even if he is a shaman,
he's still just human.

00:49:11.595 --> 00:49:12.930
How dangerous can he be?

00:49:13.889 --> 00:49:17.268
I'm not sure, but we should
take precautions just in case.

00:49:18.435 --> 00:49:21.855
So, I'm going to hide your fox bead
without telling you where.

00:49:21.939 --> 00:49:26.151
How? Whether you keep it
or hide it somewhere,

00:49:26.235 --> 00:49:27.778
I'd be able to sense it.

00:49:29.655 --> 00:49:33.576
I need to sever your connection
to the bead, just for a while.

00:49:40.874 --> 00:49:42.126
You trust me, right?

00:49:47.756 --> 00:49:50.384
Eun-ho… Eun-ho!

00:49:52.011 --> 00:49:54.221
What am I supposed to do?

00:49:56.140 --> 00:49:59.393
The dagger. That should do it.

00:50:28.088 --> 00:50:29.048
This is…

00:50:29.131 --> 00:50:32.885
It's the only Sajin Ritual Blade
left in the world.

00:50:32.968 --> 00:50:35.846
It's a sacred dagger
that can sever and defy fate.

00:50:51.445 --> 00:50:53.656
You'll die at this rate.

00:50:54.406 --> 00:50:56.825
Wouldn't it be better
to just give me the bead?

00:50:57.826 --> 00:51:01.038
Tell him to put it in your hand. Quickly!

00:51:01.121 --> 00:51:02.831
- Hurry!
- In my hand?

00:51:12.508 --> 00:51:13.717
- In my hand…
- What?

00:51:16.136 --> 00:51:17.262
In my hand.

00:51:18.347 --> 00:51:19.556
In my hand…

00:52:04.685 --> 00:52:06.145
What's wrong?

00:52:09.398 --> 00:52:12.276
What's happening? Hey!

00:52:13.944 --> 00:52:16.321
- Something's wrong.
- What?

00:52:16.405 --> 00:52:17.740
The plan's ruined.

00:52:18.949 --> 00:52:20.492
Damn it.

00:52:21.368 --> 00:52:22.619
Hey!

00:52:27.708 --> 00:52:28.792
Eun-ho.

00:52:29.418 --> 00:52:31.837
Are you okay? Are you with me?

00:52:31.920 --> 00:52:33.589
- Sis.
- Si-yeol.

00:52:35.340 --> 00:52:38.051
Sis, are you okay?

00:52:39.803 --> 00:52:42.890
What happened? Why did you suddenly--

00:52:42.973 --> 00:52:44.183
It's all over.

00:52:45.267 --> 00:52:46.393
What?

00:52:47.728 --> 00:52:50.689
We're safe now.

00:52:58.864 --> 00:53:01.617
- Calm down!
- Get away!

00:53:01.700 --> 00:53:04.536
Get away from me!

00:53:05.788 --> 00:53:07.790
I don't have any power left.

00:53:07.873 --> 00:53:11.126
Just leave me alone!

00:53:13.378 --> 00:53:17.049
Damn it. Just… kill me!

00:53:17.132 --> 00:53:20.427
Just leave me alone to die.

00:53:21.345 --> 00:53:23.347
What the hell happened?

00:53:24.014 --> 00:53:28.852
Please, I was wrong. I'm sorry.

00:53:30.354 --> 00:53:32.105
I'm sorry.

00:53:32.856 --> 00:53:35.692
It was my fault. I was wrong.

00:53:51.792 --> 00:53:53.961
Man, cleaning everything up took forever.

00:53:54.044 --> 00:53:56.755
Are you sure nothing's missing?

00:53:58.006 --> 00:53:59.091
Yeah.

00:54:00.133 --> 00:54:02.761
Eun-ho seems pretty shaken up, though.

00:54:02.845 --> 00:54:04.263
Of course she is.

00:54:04.346 --> 00:54:06.807
The place was trashed
while they were gone.

00:54:07.766 --> 00:54:09.476
Anyway, let's get going.

00:54:09.560 --> 00:54:11.603
You rest up too, Si-yeol.
You must be pretty shaken.

00:54:11.687 --> 00:54:13.146
No, let's head out together.

00:54:13.897 --> 00:54:16.149
I need to get groceries
to make her something to eat.

00:54:16.233 --> 00:54:17.442
- Sure thing.
- Okay.

00:54:20.529 --> 00:54:22.072
Thanks.

00:54:46.179 --> 00:54:48.432
That'll be 22,980 won.

00:54:50.267 --> 00:54:52.644
Wait… what?

00:54:53.604 --> 00:54:56.273
Oh man. I forgot my wallet.

00:55:20.255 --> 00:55:22.716
I'm coming, okay?

00:55:22.799 --> 00:55:24.635
Who is it at this hour?

00:55:26.887 --> 00:55:27.888
What?

00:55:28.889 --> 00:55:30.599
And where did Si-yeol go?

00:55:32.392 --> 00:55:36.688
Gosh, all right! I'm coming!

00:55:45.030 --> 00:55:46.281
What are you doing?

00:55:46.907 --> 00:55:48.367
I was thinking about this all wrong.

00:55:48.450 --> 00:55:50.869
Forget waiting for my turn.

00:55:50.953 --> 00:55:52.371
Let's just end this right now.

00:55:55.666 --> 00:55:57.042
What do you think you're doing?

00:55:57.125 --> 00:55:59.670
If you're doing this
because you still trust that shaman--

00:55:59.753 --> 00:56:00.837
Trust who?

00:56:04.299 --> 00:56:07.052
That bastard's barely conscious.
He's just breathing with his eyes open.

00:56:07.135 --> 00:56:09.137
He's basically a vegetable.

00:56:09.221 --> 00:56:11.014
You guys did that to him!

00:56:13.767 --> 00:56:16.853
No. He brought that on himself.

00:56:17.896 --> 00:56:20.148
Just like you're doing right now.

00:56:21.191 --> 00:56:24.611
I don't care.
I'm not going to end up like that.

00:56:27.531 --> 00:56:28.699
This is the way of humans.

00:56:29.825 --> 00:56:33.245
Let's see if you can still use
that sorcery of yours

00:56:34.579 --> 00:56:36.331
with a hole in your head.

00:56:46.466 --> 00:56:47.509
Hey!

00:56:47.592 --> 00:56:48.760
You little--

00:57:00.188 --> 00:57:01.523
Si-yeol!

00:57:37.893 --> 00:57:39.311
Si-yeol…

00:57:40.187 --> 00:57:41.855
Si-yeol, why did you do that?

00:57:43.398 --> 00:57:44.441
Are you…

00:57:45.400 --> 00:57:46.443
Are you okay?

00:57:47.444 --> 00:57:51.990
Why are you worrying about me right now?
You're the one who got shot!

00:57:54.409 --> 00:57:56.620
This wasn't in the future I saw.

00:57:56.703 --> 00:57:59.664
Why is it you instead of me?

00:58:00.624 --> 00:58:02.959
He will eventually die.

00:58:03.585 --> 00:58:06.046
That's the fate

00:58:06.963 --> 00:58:08.131
you gave him.

00:58:10.717 --> 00:58:12.427
How can you do this?

00:58:13.178 --> 00:58:15.347
After you finally made me human

00:58:15.430 --> 00:58:18.809
and made me fall in love with a human,
how could you do this?

00:58:39.788 --> 00:58:41.289
Si-yeol.

00:58:42.624 --> 00:58:44.960
Si-yeol…

00:58:57.472 --> 00:58:59.724
No, Si-yeol… what do I do?

00:59:08.108 --> 00:59:09.985
{\an8}SPECIAL APPEARANCE BY HONG SU-HYEON

00:59:34.384 --> 00:59:37.304
NO TAIL TO TELL

00:59:37.387 --> 00:59:39.764
{\an8}- Please, save him.
- You can't come in.

00:59:39.848 --> 00:59:42.100
{\an8}There will come a time
when you must choose.

00:59:42.184 --> 00:59:44.895
{\an8}If Si-yeol just dies like this,

00:59:44.978 --> 00:59:46.897
{\an8}then there's really nothing we can do.

00:59:46.980 --> 00:59:49.357
{\an8}Even if I die, I want to die as myself.

00:59:50.817 --> 00:59:52.277
{\an8}That's my wish.

00:59:52.360 --> 00:59:53.904
{\an8}It's so strange

00:59:53.987 --> 00:59:58.033
{\an8}that the only people left
who remember Eun-ho are you and me.

00:59:58.658 --> 01:00:01.620
{\an8}You need to let go too.

01:00:02.120 --> 01:00:04.915
{\an8}This is the end for me. My final moment.

01:00:04.998 --> 01:00:05.999
{\an8}RIP KANG SI-YEOL

01:00:06.082 --> 01:00:08.335
{\an8}I never once imagined an ending like this.

01:00:10.629 --> 01:00:12.631
{\an8}Subtitle translation by Susanna Kim